4. Lorenzo Concia

# Lorenzo Concia

## Research Associate Life Sciences Computing

Email: **[lconcia@tacc.utexas.edu](mailto:lconcia@tacc.utexas.edu)**

Lorenzo is a computational biologist with a background in experimental molecular biology. He uses multi-OMICS data to tackle the study of plant genomes under multiple aspects, including genomics, epigenomics, gene expression, and chromosome conformation. He has a specific interest in crops and in large and complex genomes, such as corn (Zea mays) and wheat (Triticum aestivum).

After earning a PhD in Genetics and Molecular Biology at the University of Pavia in Italy he worked at North Carolina State University, Université Paris-Saclay, and École Normale Supérieure in France. He joined TACC in 2023 as a Research Associate to work at the interface between genomics, epigenomics, and computational biology.

